@fatcat2248 wrote:

you could also try this?

First download java at www.java.com
Then open up My Computer.

Click System Information

Click the Advanced Tab

Click Enviromental Variables

Click New at the top

Then for variable Name put CLASSPATH and for the path put CLASSPATH=C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_09\bin;%CLASSPATH%;.
Now click Ok and click New one more time put as the variable name Path and the path put C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_09\bin

Now you should be able to runserver and compile.

item.title: Mod please remove
item.dc:creator: @Cyber_Punk Cyber Punk
item.description:
@Cyber_Punk wrote:

i had the same problem, so this is what i did. Right click the compiler and press edit.

here is what it should look like

@echo off
COLOR 09
title PhoneScape Compiler
javac *.java
pause

Now go and find out where your Jdk 6u1 was installed (the path). for example mine was “c:\java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin” then add that before the word javac. it should look something like this.

@echo off
COLOR 09
title PhoneScape Compiler
c:\java\jdk1.6.0_01\bin\javac *.java
pause

Then save, compile and Voila, youve got your compiler running.
